Former Post Office CEO Mark Barnes has spoken out for the first time since his resignation was announced. Courtesy of #DSTV403 JOHANNESBURG - Outgoing South African Post Office CEO Mark Barnes said he has mixed feelings about leaving. Barnes has spoken out for the first time since his resignation was announced. READ: Post Office CEO resigns He is credited for steering the troubled state-owned enterprise from near collapse. "I am sad to go and a little angry," he said. READ: Scopa forces Dlamini, Post Office to find amicable solution Barnes said a post service that is just post service has no great future. "However, the combination of their footprints and access if you integrate them with e-commerce and financial services and logistics... it becomes an institutional future."